  "chapter": {
    "number": 3,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "God’s Fellow Workers"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "Brothers, I could not address you as spiritual, but as worldly—as infants in Christ."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          "I gave you milk, not solid food, for you were not yet ready for solid food. In fact, you are still not ready,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          "for you are still worldly. For since there is jealousy and dissension among you, are you not worldly? Are you not walking in the way of man?"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          "For when one of you says, “I follow Paul,” and another, “I follow Apollos,” are you not mere men?"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          "What then is Apollos? And what is Paul? They are servants through whom you believed, as the Lord has assigned to each his role."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          "I planted the seed and Apollos watered it, but God made it grow."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          "So neither he who plants nor he who waters is anything, but only God, who makes things grow."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          "He who plants and he who waters are one in purpose,",
          {
            "noteId": 238
          },
          "and each will be rewarded according to his own labor."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          "For we are God’s fellow workers; you are God’s field, God’s building."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Christ Our Foundation"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          "By the grace God has given me, I laid a foundation as an expert builder, and someone else is building on it. But each one must be careful how he builds."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          "For no one can lay a foundation other than the one already laid, which is Jesus Christ."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          "If anyone builds on this foundation using gold, silver, precious stones, wood, hay, or straw,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          "his workmanship will be evident, because the Day will bring it to light. It will be revealed with fire, and the fire will prove the quality of each man’s work."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          "If what he has built survives, he will receive a reward."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          "If it is burned up, he will suffer loss. He himself will be saved, but only as if through the flames."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "God’s Temple and God’s Wisdom"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          "Do you not know that you yourselves are God’s temple, and that God’s Spirit dwells in",
          {
            "noteId": 239
          },
          "you?"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          "If anyone destroys God’s temple, God will destroy him; for God’s temple is holy, and you are that temple."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          "Let no one deceive himself. If any of you thinks he is wise in this age, he should become a fool, so that he may become wise."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          "For the wisdom of this world is foolishness in God’s sight. As it is written: “He catches the wise in their craftiness.”",
          {
            "noteId": 240
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          "And again, “The Lord knows that the thoughts of the wise are futile.”",
          {
            "noteId": 241
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          "Therefore, stop boasting in men. All things are yours,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          "whether Paul or Apollos or Cephas",
          {
            "noteId": 242
          },
          "or the world or life or death or the present or the future. All of them belong to you,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          "and you belong to Christ, and Christ belongs to God."
        ]
      }
    ],
